            <title>[SOLR-4575] SOLR-4196 took away the ability to use solr.core.name (and others) in solrconfig &amp; etc.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4575</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;solr.core.name&lt;br/&gt;
solr.core.instanceDir&lt;br/&gt;
solr.core.dataDir&lt;br/&gt;
solr.core.configName&lt;br/&gt;
solr.core.schemaName&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;all are introduced (without necessarily reading them from the environment) so they can be referenced in various config files (e.g. solrconfig.xml) or passed through as system vars.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Shawn:&lt;br/&gt;
Thans for pointing at that specific revision, made it much easier for me to pinpoint.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
