                            <comment id="13601749" author="elyograg" created="Wed, 13 Mar 2013 22:34:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch restoring old behavior with the current code lines commented out. Patch is against 4.x but applies cleanly to trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13601803" author="elyograg" created="Wed, 13 Mar 2013 23:28:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch didn&apos;t work.  For those following along, the following in solrcofig.xml, indexConfig section, is what doesn&apos;t work after upgrading from 4.2-SNAPSHOT to 4.3-SNAPSHOT:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;  &amp;lt;infoStream file=&quot;INFOSTREAM-${solr.core.name}.txt&quot;&amp;gt;false&amp;lt;/infoStream&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13601902" author="erickerickson" created="Thu, 14 Mar 2013 00:43:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Preliminary patch. At least it assigns the correct value in the debugger. Needs tests before committing but if you want to try it out please do.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13601969" author="erickerickson" created="Thu, 14 Mar 2013 02:15:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Final (I hope) patch with tests. Lots of very important implicit properties won&apos;t work without this, basically all of the solr.core.&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;instanceDir|dataDir|configName|schemaName|name&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was built on trunk, but should apply to 4x cleanly (although I haven&apos;t tried it).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll commit to trunk and merge these into 4x after I&apos;ve run all the tests, probably not until the morning though, I&apos;d like to look it over again after some sleep.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for pointing this out Shawn! I&apos;m really glad this didn&apos;t get into a release.....&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13601974" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Thu, 14 Mar 2013 02:22:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We might want to consider letting this change wait until after 4.3. It would be nice to get 4.3 out soon, but I&apos;d hate to rush this change. I don&apos;t think many others have had a chance to check it out or comment on it yet - I know I have not. Before we get some back compat pains out there, we should really get more people looking at these changes and make sure it&apos;s what we really want to move to. I think a key reason not many people have looked at this yet is that the example is not setup for it - I really think if we are going to support it, we need to move the example and tests to it and force people/devs to see it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13602205" author="erickerickson" created="Thu, 14 Mar 2013 11:46:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Mark:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Actually, I had it completely backwards. Restoring this behavior doesn&apos;t require that you define, for instance, &quot;solr.core.name&quot; in core.properties, you should still just use &quot;name&quot;. These are the &quot;implicit properties&quot; that you can refer to in, for instance, solrconfig.xml.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The only real back-compat cost at this point is carrying around two entries for each of the listed properties in coredescriptor, e.g.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;name =&amp;gt; collection1&lt;br/&gt;
and&lt;br/&gt;
solr.core.name =&amp;gt; collection1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In fact, in this example in solrconfig.xml, you could ask for&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;infoStream file=&quot;INFOSTREAM-${solr.core.name}.txt&quot;&amp;gt;false&amp;lt;/infoStream&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
or&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;infoStream file=&quot;INFOSTREAM-${name}.txt&quot;&amp;gt;false&amp;lt;/infoStream&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
and get the same results.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So with that cost I think we should put this behavior back rather than pull the rug out from under existing behavior. If we want to yank it for 5.0 all we have to do is remove CoreContainer.initImplicitProperties. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13602283" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Thu, 14 Mar 2013 13:59:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, wasn&apos;t very clear - I was being more broad - talking about the entire solr.xml goes away issue rather than this particular nit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13602353" author="commit-tag-bot" created="Thu, 14 Mar 2013 15:40:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;trunk commit&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Erick Erickson&lt;br/&gt;
